about six feet down.

10
00:02:31,562 --> 00:02:32,692
In an old disco?

11
00:02:32,692 --> 00:02:34,846
Was an old disco, The Bell.

12
00:02:34,846 --> 00:02:36,581
Off Lansing Boulevard, real eyesore?

13
00:02:36,581 --> 00:02:37,690
That's the spot.

14
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:40,959
22 people were killed 
there in a fire, 1978.

15
00:02:40,959 --> 00:02:42,671
Ruled as arson.

16
00:02:42,671 --> 00:02:45,805
23rd was presumed dead,
remains were never found.

17
00:02:45,805 --> 00:02:47,567
You thinking this must be the guy?

18
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:48,771
John Doe.

19
00:02:48,771 --> 00:02:50,036
That's all that's left of him?

20
00:02:50,036 --> 00:02:53,154
Skull's all I need to get an ID.
Man had excellent teeth.

21
00:02:53,154 --> 00:02:55,438
If he burned up in the fire, why 
didn't we find him back then?

22
00:02:55,438 --> 00:03:00,076
Well, apprently he was deep 
underground where the VIP room was.

23
00:03:00,076 --> 00:03:02,614
Plus, what is that?

24
00:03:02,614 --> 00:03:05,991
Slug's been rolling 
around in his brain pan.

25
00:03:06,824 --> 00:03:08,578
Right between the eyes.

26
00:03:08,578 --> 00:03:10,188
Shooter must have been close up.

27
00:03:10,188 --> 00:03:12,066
Can we get rifling off this slug?

28
00:03:12,066 --> 00:03:15,084
My guess is it's a .38.
Should have distinct markings.

29
00:03:15,084 --> 00:03:17,476
This guy was probably shot 
before the fire ever got to him.

30
00:03:17,476 --> 00:03:20,120
Well, maybe our doer started 
the blaze, covered his tracks.

31
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:23,016
Hide one murder, cause 22 others.

32
00:03:23,016 --> 00:03:25,088
We don't got a cold one here.

33
