43
00:03:59,002 --> 00:04:01,038
Dental records were conclusive.

44
00:04:01,038 --> 00:04:03,855
This is our John Doe.

45
00:04:04,055 --> 00:04:06,668
Benjamin Issac Rosen.

46
00:04:06,668 --> 00:04:08,108
Twenty-two.

47
00:04:08,108 --> 00:04:10,667
I remember the news 
coverage of The Bell fire.

48
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:13,032
Cryin' families, burned bodies.

49
00:04:13,032 --> 00:04:15,291
Bulldozers come in quick, 
demolish the place?

50
00:04:15,291 --> 00:04:19,125
Yeah. What was left standing 
was considered a safety hazard.

51
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:22,122
So maybe they did a rush 
job finding all the remains.

52
00:04:22,122 --> 00:04:24,635
Explains why they didn't find him.

53
00:04:25,152 --> 00:04:27,892
You, uh, ever hang out 
at this disco, boss?

54
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:28,982
Oh, not me.

55
00:04:28,982 --> 00:04:32,079
But I think Jeffries was a beat 
cop in South at the time.

56
00:04:32,079 --> 00:04:35,035
I wonder what he did Saturday nights.

57
00:04:35,035 --> 00:04:38,441
The Bell wasn't just a disco, 
it was the disco.

58
00:04:38,441 --> 00:04:40,234
Lines around the block to get in.

59
00:04:40,234 --> 00:04:43,633
Lot of feathered hair, 
gold chains, polyester...

60
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:46,874
Sounds like you got 
some familiarity there, Will.

61
00:04:46,874 --> 00:04:48,646
I was there once.

62
00:04:48,646 --> 00:04:51,133
William Disco Jeffries.

63
00:04:51,133 --> 00:04:52,846
Come on, Will, bust a move for us.

64
00:04:52,846 --> 00:04:54,574
Yeah, do the hustle, baby.

65
00:04:54,574 --> 00:04:57,445
You know, if it's all the 
same, I'd rather not.

66
00:04:57,445 --> 00:05:00,531
Those were regrettable times.

67
00:05:00,531 --> 00:05:03,495
The arson report says the 
blaze started in the White Room.

68
00:05:03,495 --> 00:05:04,339
Do you know what that was?

69
00:05:04,339 --> 00:05:06,699
VIP lounge, where all the 
cocaine was snorted.

70
00:05:06,699 --> 00:05:08,884
And where's Ben Rosen's 
remains were found.

71
00:05:08,884 --> 00:05:12,241
- So, maybe he started the fire.
- Right after he got shot in the face.

72
00:05:12,241 --> 00:05:12,974
That's a point.

73
00:05:12,974 --> 00:05:15,486
So who was with Ben 
in the White Room?

74
00:05:15,486 --> 00:05:18,108
Chief suspect in the arson 
was the owner of the place.

75
00:05:18,108 --> 00:05:19,398
Neil Chaney.

76
00:05:19,398 --> 00:05:21,517
Torched his own club 
for the insurance?

77
00:05:21,517 --> 00:05:23,308
You'd think he'd wait 
till after hours.

78
00:05:23,308 --> 00:05:26,968
Looks like they dug, but 
didn't get far with that theory.

79
00:05:26,968 --> 00:05:29,172
We got partial rifling 
on the bullet.

80
00:05:29,172 --> 00:05:31,218
It was a .38. / Good 
enough to find a match?

81
00:05:31,218 --> 00:05:34,151
Yep. We find the gun 
that matches this slug,

82
00:05:34,151 --> 00:05:35,139
could lead us to the doer.

83
00:05:35,139 --> 00:05:37,053
I'd call that new direction.

84
00:05:37,053 --> 00:05:40,525
Vera, Disco Will, have a 
conversation with Neil Chaney.

85
00:05:40,525 --> 00:05:43,911
- Meantime... 
- We'll go to the Rosens.

86
00:05:46,293 --> 00:05:50,786
You found Benny,
after all these years?

87
00:05:50,786 --> 00:05:57,175
I always hoped, prayed, he got 
out of that conflagration somehow.

88
00:05:57,175 --> 00:06:00,480
Ran away or something.

89
00:06:01,006 --> 00:06:03,372
Foolish. I know.

90
00:06:03,372 --> 00:06:04,698
Benny lived at home with you?

91
00:06:04,698 --> 00:06:06,668
He was going to go to dental school.

92
00:06:06,668 --> 00:06:08,455
Top of his class.

93
00:06:08,455 --> 00:06:11,373
Smart. Sweet.

94
00:06:11,373 --> 00:06:14,338
He have any enemies you know of?

95
00:06:14,338 --> 00:06:16,341
I thought he died in the fire.

96
00:06:16,341 --> 00:06:21,001
I'm afraid he was murdered, 
Mrs. Rogen, before the fire started.

97
00:06:21,001 --> 00:06:22,423
Murdered?

98
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:24,001
Was he in any kind of trouble?

99
00:06:24,001 --> 00:06:26,046
How should we know?

100
00:06:26,046 --> 00:06:31,249
Benny was an open book before he 
started playing that so-called music.

101
00:06:31,249 --> 00:06:34,846
After, he shut us out.

102
00:06:34,846 --> 00:06:36,787
He knew we disapproved.

103
00:06:36,787 --> 00:06:39,635
Why shouldn't I have disapproved?

104
00:06:39,635 --> 00:06:41,945
That disco ruined his life.

105
00:06:41,945 --> 00:06:46,432
We, uh, kept some of 
his things in his room.

106
00:06:46,432 --> 00:06:49,681
Maybe you'd like to see?

107
00:07:02,459 --> 00:07:07,127
Salutatorian of 
his high school class.

108
00:07:10,382 --> 00:07:12,677
Adorable, right?

109
00:07:12,677 --> 00:07:15,384
There something you 
wanna tell us, Myra?

110
00:07:15,384 --> 00:07:18,319
Something you didn't want 
your husband to hear?

111
00:07:18,319 --> 00:07:20,152
No, of course not.

112
00:07:20,152 --> 00:07:23,904
'Cause I got the feeling there was.

113
00:07:26,157 --> 00:07:29,194
We know this is difficult.

114
00:07:29,935 --> 00:07:32,882
Doesn't have to leave this room.

115
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:37,777
There was something.

116
00:07:39,692 --> 00:07:42,155
It's something I never told my husband.

117
00:07:42,155 --> 00:07:44,265
What was that?

118
00:07:44,265 --> 00:07:49,563
I came home from temple early 
one night, on account of my arthritis.

119
00:07:49,563 --> 00:07:51,575
This was a week before the fire.

120
00:07:51,575 --> 00:07:54,083
And, uh...

121
00:07:55,029 --> 00:07:57,195
I saw them together.

122
00:07:57,195 --> 00:08:01,628
My Benny, and a shiksa.

123
00:08:01,904 --> 00:08:03,685
Like you.

124
00:08:28,329 --> 00:08:32,765
Mmm, not here, baby. / Come on.
My folks won't be back for hours.

125
00:08:33,131 --> 00:08:36,609
But if we want to win this 
competition, we got to practice.

126
00:08:36,609 --> 00:08:38,246
I don't got the rhythm like you do.

127
00:08:38,246 --> 00:08:41,183
You got it where it counts, baby.
You're far out.

128
00:08:41,183 --> 00:08:43,755
When you gonna tell your 
parents we're engaged?

129
00:08:43,755 --> 00:08:45,047
Soon.

130
00:08:45,047 --> 00:08:48,193
You are such a foxy mama.

131
00:08:48,193 --> 00:08:49,070
Benny...

132
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:53,604
Hey, you know I wanna marry you,

133
00:08:53,604 --> 00:08:56,992
spend my whole life 
dancing with you.

134
00:08:59,686 --> 00:09:03,300
We don't have to make it 
now if you don't want to.

135
00:09:05,258 --> 00:09:09,363
We'll practice, 
then we'll make it, huh?

136
00:09:09,363 --> 00:09:12,451
I love you, hot stuff.

137
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:15,707
They were in love.

138
00:09:15,707 --> 00:09:19,736
At least my Benny had 
that before he died.

139
00:09:19,736 --> 00:09:23,177
Did Benny ever talk about 
his wedding plans?

140
00:09:23,177 --> 00:09:28,236
He was probably afraid to.
His father would have hit the roof.

141
00:09:28,236 --> 00:09:30,091
You know what happened 
to this girl, Sonya?

142
00:09:30,091 --> 00:09:32,507
She got burned in the fire.

143
00:09:32,763 --> 00:09:35,626
I visited her once 
at Saint Ignatius,

144
00:09:35,626 --> 00:09:38,324
she was all doped up.
Never knew I was there.

145
00:09:38,324 --> 00:09:40,578
And your husband still 
doesn't know about her?

146
00:09:40,578 --> 00:09:43,007
He needs more heartache?

147
00:09:43,007 --> 00:09:49,167
It's bad enough feeling his son 
betrayed him over disco.

148
00:09:58,805 --> 00:10:01,005
Sonya Witkowski?

149
00:10:01,005 --> 00:10:02,760
Yes.

150
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:05,242
Detectives Rush and Valens.

151
00:10:05,242 --> 00:10:07,679
We're here about Benjamin Rosen.

152
00:10:07,679 --> 00:10:09,922
Benny?

153
00:10:13,051 --> 00:10:15,477
I'll be right back.

154
00:10:19,829 --> 00:10:22,964
I lost Benny in The Bell fire.

155
00:10:22,964 --> 00:10:25,650
Part of his remains were 
recently found, Sonya.

156
00:10:25,650 --> 00:10:29,839
It appears he was killed
before the fire started.

157
00:10:30,211 --> 00:10:32,529
Someone killed him?

158
00:10:32,822 --> 00:10:35,365
I'm afraid so.

159
00:10:35,613 --> 00:10:37,802
We understand you two were engaged.

160
00:10:37,802 --> 00:10:42,228
We were gonna get married 
after the dance competition.

161
00:10:42,228 --> 00:10:44,636
That was such a long time ago.

162
00:10:44,636 --> 00:10:49,179
Was there anything unusual going on 
in Benny's life, right around then?

163
00:10:49,179 --> 00:10:50,832
Fights? A threat?

164
00:10:50,832 --> 00:10:53,995
No. I mean...

165
00:10:54,311 --> 00:10:55,893
You sure he was murdered?

166
00:10:55,893 --> 00:10:59,531
Anything you can tell 
us could really help.

167
00:11:01,305 --> 00:11:04,900
A couple of days before 
the dance contest,

168
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:07,436
I got there early to practice...

169
00:11:25,777 --> 00:11:28,768
Hey, foxy mama, let's hustle.

170
00:11:28,768 --> 00:11:31,106
What did Chaney want?

171
00:11:31,327 --> 00:11:32,477
Nothing.

172
00:11:32,477 --> 00:11:35,573
- Didn't look like nothing.
- Are we talking or are we dancing?

173
00:11:35,573 --> 00:11:37,469
You deal blow for Chaney, 
Benny, I'll dump your ass.

174
00:11:37,469 --> 00:11:39,770
I'm not dealin' blow.

175
00:11:39,770 --> 00:11:41,872
I swear.

176
00:11:42,354 --> 00:11:44,356
You wouldn't lie to me?

177
00:11:44,356 --> 00:11:46,887
I'd rather die.

178
00:11:52,761 --> 00:11:55,403
Hey, after we win that 
thousand bucks, baby,

179
00:11:55,403 --> 00:11:57,368
let's elope. 
We'll go to the Manhattan,

180
00:11:57,368 --> 00:11:59,637
get married at Studio 54.

181
00:11:59,637 --> 00:12:00,688
We gotta win first.

182
00:12:00,688 --> 00:12:04,099
We'll win. You're the best 
disco dancer in Philly.

183
00:12:04,099 --> 00:12:06,300
Philly? Is that all?

184
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:11,222
In America. The whole world.

185
00:12:12,543 --> 00:12:15,495
He was the love of my life, 
you know?

186
00:12:15,495 --> 00:12:16,907
The real deal.

187
00:12:16,907 --> 00:12:19,663
What were Benny and 
Mr. Chaney fighting about?

188
00:12:19,663 --> 00:12:21,169
I don't know.

189
00:12:21,169 --> 00:12:26,199
Benny used to give private dance 
lessons to some of Chaney's clients,

190
00:12:26,728 --> 00:12:29,005
but it seemed like 
something more serious.

191
00:12:29,005 --> 00:12:32,371
Are you sure it ain't possible
Benny was dealing for him?

192
00:12:32,371 --> 00:12:35,186
He said he wasn't.

193
00:12:36,251 --> 00:12:39,617
On the off chance that he was, Sonya,

194
00:12:39,617 --> 00:12:43,181
you think Chaney was the kind of 
man who could murder someone?

195
00:12:43,181 --> 00:12:45,689
I know he had a gun.

196
00:12:45,689 --> 00:12:48,923
Used to show it off,
like some kind of big shot.

197
00:12:50,447 --> 00:12:54,070
We're still looking for Neil Chaney,
but he did have a permit for a .38.

198
00:12:54,070 --> 00:12:57,777
Which he fired in '77.
Shot a burglar at The Bell.

199
00:12:57,777 --> 00:13:00,842
- A year before Benny was shot.
- File's coming over from South.

200
00:13:00,842 --> 00:13:02,868
We find the slug 
he shot at the burglar,

201
00:13:02,868 --> 00:13:04,442
match it to the one 
we got on this job...

202
00:13:04,442 --> 00:13:06,664
Makes Chaney a good bet for the doer.

203
00:13:06,664 --> 00:13:09,997
We're talking about finding a bullet
fired 26 years ago from a gun

204
00:13:09,997 --> 00:13:11,790
we don't even know exists anymore.

205
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:13,771
Registered to a man we can't find.

206
00:13:13,771 --> 00:13:15,083
Yeah.

207
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:17,265
The word "longshot" comes to mind.

208
00:13:17,265 --> 00:13:18,715
We like a challenge.

209
00:13:18,715 --> 00:13:20,839
Well, you got one.

210
00:13:29,474 --> 00:13:33,063
File from South IDs this guy 
Chaney shot as Mark Rigley.

211
00:13:33,063 --> 00:13:35,437
Tried to rob a disco at closing.
Chaney popped him.

212
00:13:35,437 --> 00:13:37,053
Shooting was ruled self-defense.

213
00:13:37,053 --> 00:13:38,874
Maybe Rigley knows what 
happened to the slug.

214
00:13:38,874 --> 00:13:40,021
He doin' time someplace?

215
00:13:40,021 --> 00:13:43,582
Uh-uh. Custodial detail at 
the River Rink, Penn's Landing.

216
00:13:43,582 --> 00:13:45,597
Know how we been having 
trouble findin' Chaney?

217
00:13:45,597 --> 00:13:48,691
It's 'cause County's six months 
behind processing death certificates.

218
00:13:48,691 --> 00:13:49,834
Chaney's dead?

219
00:13:49,834 --> 00:13:51,897
Three months ago.
Cirrhosis of the liver.

220
00:13:51,897 --> 00:13:53,531
Crap.

221
00:13:53,531 --> 00:13:57,152
So what?
We still have 23 unsolved murders.

222
00:13:57,152 --> 00:13:59,162
We can't talk to the father,
we'll settle for the son.

223
00:13:59,162 --> 00:14:00,019
He's not dead, is he?

224
00:14:00,019 --> 00:14:03,089
No. Paul Chaney owns 
a shop in Center City.

225
00:14:03,089 --> 00:14:04,160
Good.

226
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:05,785
Out on the street, boss.

227
00:14:15,666 --> 00:14:18,548
Excuse me just one second.
Enjoy yourselves.

228
00:14:20,564 --> 00:14:22,462
Whassup, folks?

229
00:14:22,462 --> 00:14:24,241
You want a pipe?

230
00:14:24,822 --> 00:14:26,162
Depends what's in it.

231
00:14:26,162 --> 00:14:29,528
Tobacco, the new marijuana.

232
00:14:29,711 --> 00:14:32,191
That's far out, Paul.

233
00:14:32,650 --> 00:14:34,818
Tobacco's legal, remember?

234
00:14:34,818 --> 00:14:36,767
Hey, you wanna check 
the pipes, be my guest.

235
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:38,886
- We ain't narcs.
- We're homicide.

236
00:14:38,886 --> 00:14:40,416
Homicide?

237
00:14:40,961 --> 00:14:42,014
What do you want with me?

238
00:14:42,014 --> 00:14:45,139
Your father. 
He had a permit for a .38.

239
00:14:45,139 --> 00:14:47,686
We thought you might know 
where that gun is now.

240
00:14:47,686 --> 00:14:52,548
Uh, excuse me. You mind just 
stepping over here for a second?

241
00:14:55,476 --> 00:14:56,615
Why? What's this about?

242
00:14:56,615 --> 00:14:57,901
The Bell.

243
00:14:58,183 --> 00:15:01,152
A man was killed there that 
night before the fire broke out.

244
00:15:01,152 --> 00:15:03,701
And you want to pin it on my old 
man who's trying to rest in peace?

245
00:15:03,701 --> 00:15:07,302
- We're trying to solve a murder.
- Don't you mean murders?

